<BYLINE>
   By ROLAND RUDD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ALLIED COLLOIDS, the speciality chemicals group, reported a 7 per cent
increase in pre-tax profits, from Pounds 21.1m to Pounds 22.5m, in the half
year to October 3.
The group said its lack of dependence on the UK enabled it to sustain volume
growth.
Sales, up 9 per cent, from Pounds 124.6m to Pounds 136.3m, had increased in
all regions. Only 16 per cent of the group's turnover is based in the UK.
The company said: 'Although we can as yet discern little favourable change
in market conditions around the world, we nevertheless expect to be able to
sustain the improvement for the remainder of the year.'
Hydrolabs, the US speciality chemicals company supplying the textile
industry which was acquired last year for Dollars 18m, broke even after
start-up costs. The group is planning to expand this company in order to
market its products around the world.
The tax charge increased from Pounds 7.7m to Pounds 8.2m after an
exceptionally low payment at the end of the last financial year. This was
because a provision for deferred taxation of Pounds 5m relating to
accelerated capital allowances was no longer required.
Earnings per share increased to 5.47p (5.17p). The interim dividend is 0.94p
(0.88p).
