FT  02 DEC 92 / UK Company News: Smith &amp; Nephew in Pounds 46.5m Nivea sale
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD GOURLAY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SMITH &amp; NEPHEW, the healthcare and toiletries company, has sold its share of
the Nivea skincare product brand to its joint venture partner, Beirsdorf of
Hamburg, for Pounds 46.5m.
The UK-based company will continue to distribute Nivea products in the UK,
South Africa and Commonwealth countries where it owns the brand and it will
continue to manufacture in Australia and South Africa where Beirsdorf has no
production facilities.
Mr John Robinson, chief executive, said that because profits from Nivea were
relatively low, the interest on the sale proceeds combined with the profits
from distribution would be greater than the profits stream from ownership of
its part of the brand.
'This is part of a wider strategy to focus on our healthcare businesses and
yet maintain our critical mass in the consumer business in the UK,' Mr
Robinson said.
Smith &amp; Nephew's Nivea sales were Pounds 20m last year. Beirsdorf had sales
of over Pounds 300m in the rest of the world.
Mr Robinson said the sale represented a p/e multiple of 29 times and his
company was also retaining an income stream.
Smith &amp; Nephew's consumer products division, which includes its Nivea
brands, was hit by recession in the UK. This division helped restrict the
increase in pre-tax profits to only 6 per cent. The group sees its greatest
potential in its core orthopaedic and wound bandaging healthcare division.
