<HEADLINE>
FT  01 DEC 92 / UK Company News: Snack foods move boosts JLI
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PEGGY HOLLINGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A MOVE into snack foods helped JLI, the food processor and distributor which
supplies popcorn to UK film audiences, increase first half pre-tax profit by
61 per cent.
It rose from Pounds 1.14m to Pounds 1.84m in the six months ended September
30 1992 and was generated on sales 27 per cent higher at Pounds 50.9m
(Pounds 40.2m).
Mr Yoav Gottesman, chief executive, said the increases had been achieved
within a food sector suffering limited growth, low consumer confidence and
margin pressures.
He was confident the group would continue to benefit from increasing
efficiency and the strategic shift away from low-margin distribution and
into food processing.
The strongest performance came from the snacks division, built up on the
back two rights issues (raising Pounds 20.7m) and three acquisitions in
little more than a year.
Operating profits rose from Pounds 450,000 last year - which included less
than three months of Playtime, the nuts and popcorn group purchased in July
1991 - to Pounds 1.3m.
Mr Gottesman said JLI had become the UK's number one processor and supplier
of own label nuts with the acquisitions of TG Smith and Golden Twin during
the first half.
Distribution suffered a decline in sales and profits as the group abandoned
low margin business. Operating surplus fell from Pounds 840,000 to Pounds
730,000 on sales Pounds 5.6m lower at Pounds 21.3m. However, operating
margins improved from 3.1 per cent to 3.4 per cent.
The group expected to benefit from the trend towards more adventurous eating
in the UK through the acquisition in late September of Brookerpaks,
distributor of high value products such as garlic and ginger.
The ingredients division saw profits fall 14 per cent to Pounds 550,000 on
sales 38 per cent ahead to Pounds 14.9m.
The enlarged share capital depressed earnings per share from 3.4p to 3.2p.
The dividend is raised just 0.05p to 1.55p.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
