</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MATTHEW CURTIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PHILIP HARRIS, the laboratory equipment and pharmaceutical products
supplier, increased pre-tax profit by 29 per cent to Pounds 806,000 (Pounds
624,000) in the half-year to September thanks to a healthy performance from
its expanded medical division.
The interim dividend is increased 10 per cent to 2.2p (2p) and is being paid
from earnings of 6.6p (5.11).
Mr Robert Jordan, chairman, said yesterday trading con-ditions in the UK
market were difficult, but the main thrust of group activities was to
consolidate its existing businesses.
Turnover rose to Pounds 41.7m (Pounds 36.6m). Revenue from the education and
scientific division - Harris is the UK's largest supplier of scientific
equipment to schools - was flat at Pounds 11.5m (Pounds 11.3m).
Sales from the medical division - which sells pharmaceutical products to
dispensing doctors, retail chemists and health centres - jumped to Pounds
30.2m (Pounds 25.3m), after its expansion with the purchase of the Proctor
chain of pharmacies in June.
The costs of the deal pushed up interest charges to Pounds 330,000 (Pounds
287,000), which partially offset an increase in overall operating profit to
Pounds 1.14m (Pounds 911,000).
