Wickes had chosen Manders 'to ensure competitively priced, high volume and
quality production'.
Mr Roger Akers, Manders' chief executive, said that Wickes had embargoed
publicity on both how long the contract would run and how much it was worth
because it was sensitive about that information as far as its competitors
were concerned.
