</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A LEADING US manufacturer of printed circuit boards, a component of
electronic products, is to set up a plant at Livingston, West Lothian, which
is expected to employ 400 people within five years.
Jabil Circuit, of St Petersburg, Florida, is to spend Pounds 13.2m on
developing a 33,000 sq ft plant, which will be its first outside the US.
