<HEADLINE>
FT  01 DEC 92 / North Sea safety rules announced
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NEW safety rules for North Sea rigs were announced yesterday. It is
estimated they will cost the oil and gas industry Pounds 5bn.
The rules require oil operators to draw up safety plans for each of the 150
installations in the North Sea. The plans must be submitted to the Health
and Safety Executive for approval by next November.
</TEXT>
