<HEADLINE>
FT  01 DEC 92 / Benefits of merit pay questioned by Acas
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LISA WOOD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PERFORMANCE-related pay rarely achieves completely what it is meant to do,
Acas, the conciliation service, said yesterday, Lisa Wood writes.
Mr Ted Ridley, principal adviser in the Acas work research unit, said that
in spite of the popularity of performance-related pay there were often far
more effective systems of motivation and reward for managements to introduce
if they wanted to improve their organisation's performance.
He said employers should look at alternative ways of motivating and
rewarding employees.
</TEXT>
